Goal is to allow only whitelisted extensions, but don't block themes, dictionaries and locales.

title: Odkazy ikony umístěné nad obrázkem
content: Dobrý den, roky používám Firefox a mám ho jako prohlížeč nejraději. Nyní tu řeším s developerem našeho e-shopu podivnou issue. Popíšu stručně problém: https://gastro.bonno.cz/kategorie/pracovni-odevy/ Pokud si výše uvedený odkaz otevřete např. v Edge nebo Chrome, pak je možné produkty e-shopu filtrovat i pomocí ikony UNISEX umístěné na kartě produktu. To samé ale není možné ve Firefoxu. Zde se vždy otevře karta konkrétního produktu nad kterým jsem na ikonu kliknul. Developer toto označil za vaši chybu (chybu Firefoxu). Je to tak ? Nebo mi zkusíte naznačit, co má developer špatně, abych mu tuto informaci předal. Děkuji za jakoukoliv odpověď i skvělý prohlížeč. Přeji hezký den Jaroslav Ondra
creator: ondra.jaroslav

title: firefox: linux intel HD620: 3840x2160: switching issue
content:
Hi Folk,

Firefox runs perfectly smooth in 3840x2160, so this is not a perf issue. However when switching from onboard laptop screen (2k) to my external WQHD screen, Firefox does not refresh, not reacting to input or mouse until I switch back and forth from another window. So it only refresh/repaint when main window looses and gets focus.

I have to restart firefox to make it works again.

Configuration: Linux debian stable (11) (same on PopOS) CPU: intel 8550 / GPU: Intel HD 620 RAM: 16Gb External monitor connected through usb-c 3.1

It does the same with Thunderbird. My Qt apps and terminals (alacritty) are not impacted.

title: Firefox loses wifi
content:
I have Yahoo Mail+ and Gmail open in tabs (as well as MyYahoo, Yahoo Financial and Google Calendar) and both email systems intermittently declare they lose internet access. Sometimes they will continue to show current emails and sometimes not. I also have a second instance of Firefox running with MyYahoo and Start.me. All other apps on Windows 10 retain internet access as well as other non email tabs within Firefox. This does NOT happen with Chrome and the instances have increased in frequency so that I may have to switch back to using the Chrome browser. I test websites and need immediate access to email responses. I am willing to provide debug information, but don't know what or how I should report this condition. Until I get feedback I will be forced to utilize Chrome or (gasp - Edge) as my browser. I am using a Windows 10 system on an Device name Asus ROG Zephyrus Duo 15 GX550 Processor Intel(R) Core(TM) i9-10980HK CPU @ 2.40GHz 3.10 GHz Installed RAM 32.0 GB (31.8 GB usable) System type 64-bit operating system, x64-based processor Pen and touch Pen and touch support with 10 touch points

Please help me.

Oldman who knows archaic languages like Autocoder and IBM BAL 360 and Cobol
